how high error rates (60-63.16%) during the peak fault period (14:16-14:19)\n- Error rates begin to recover by 14:20-14:21\n\n### Request/Response Metrics (RRT - Round Trip Time)\nThe `rrt` metric shows:\n- **Normal baseline**: ~800-1000ms response times\n- **During fault period**: Response times increase moderately to ~1300-1400ms for shippingservice-0\n- **Notable pattern**: shippingservice-1 shows a drop in RRT to ~571ms at 14:19, then spikes to ~1496ms at 14:21\n- The RRT increases are relatively modest compared to the severe error rate spike\n\n### Network/Port-Related Metrics\nThe `pod_network_receive_bytes` metric shows:\n- **shippingservice-2**: Shows periods of 0 bytes received (14:14, 14:16-14:17, 14:19-14:20), indicating potential network connectivity issues or service unavailability\n- **shippingservice-0** and **shippingservice-1**: Maintain consistent network traffic throughout the period\n- The network receive pattern correlates with the error ratio spikes for shippingservice-2\n\n## Summary\nThe shippingservice experienced a significant error rate spike (60%+) across all three pods during the 14:13-14:19 timeframe, with shippingservice-2 showing additional network connectivity issues (periods of zero network receive bytes). The response times increased moderately but not dramatically, suggesting the issue is likely related to application-level errors rather than resource exhaustion or severe performance degradation.\n\nThe root cause appears to be a service-level issue affecting all shippingservice pods, possibly related to a dependency failure or configuration problem, as evidenced by the high error rates combined with maintained (though reduced) network connectivity."}
