n that the direct infrastructure metric queries failed, but the APM metrics clearly show widespread service failures, I should focus on what data is available. The key insight is that all cartservice and shippingservice pods are experiencing high error rates simultaneously, which suggests either:\n\n1. A shared dependency failure (like redis-cart, which also shows errors)\n2. Infrastructure issues on the nodes hosting these pods\n\nSince I cannot retrieve the infrastructure metrics directly, I\'ll base my analysis on the available APM data and the node-pod mapping.\n\n```json\n{\n  "detected_metric_keys": ["error_ratio", "client_error_ratio", "server_error_ratio", "rrt_max", "rrt"],\n  "affected_components": ["cartservice-0", "cartservice-1", "cartservice-2", "shippingservice-0", "shippingservice-1", "shippingservice-2", "redis-cart-0", "frontend-0", "frontend-1", "frontend-2"],\n  "metric_summary": "Multiple services experiencing high error ratios during fault window: cartservice pods (18-22% error ratio), shippingservice pods (40-49% error ratio), frontend pods (~28% server error ratio), and redis-cart-0 (12.8% error ratio). Response times also significantly increased for cartservice pods.",\n  "time_series_analysis": {\n    "metric_name": "error_ratio",\n    "pattern": "sudden_spike",\n    "critical_timestamps": ["2025-06-05 18:10:05"],\n    "value_change": "0.0 → 18-49%"\n  },\n  "contradictions": [\n    {\n      "evidence1": "User requested infrastructure metrics (node_memory_usage_rate, pod_processes) for specific nodes and services",\n      "evidence2": "Infrastructure metric queries failed with \'Infra pod directory not found\' error while APM metrics are available",\n      "verification_needed": "Infrastructure metrics may not be available for this time period, but APM metrics clearly show service-level failures across multiple components"\n    }\n  ],\n  "next_verification": {\n    "action": "check_logs",\n    "reason": "High error ratios across multiple s